{
  "text": "The surface of plant leaves (phyllosphere) is a preferred niche for various kinds of bacteria. Healthy leaf surface contains 10 6 to 10 7 bacterial cells/cm 2 of leaf, and the terrestrial leaf surface area that may be colonized by microbes is estimated to be approximately 6.4610 8 km 2 [CITATION_1] . Plants emit a huge amount of various volatile organic compounds, including C1 compounds such as methane [CITATION_2] and methanol. The global emission of methanol from plants is estimated to be 100 Tg per year [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] as a result of pectin degradation during plant cell elongation and division [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2304379",
